President Obama has announced his intent to nominate James X. Dempsey as a member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. Dempsey is currently the Vice President for Public Policy at the Center for Democracy & Technology and has extensive experience in privacy and national security issues. President Obama also intends to appoint Kevin J. Kennedy as a member of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. Kennedy is the President and CEO of Avaya Inc. and has a background in business communications applications and systems.